@baseUrl = http://localhost:8080/api/v1

### 0) Sanidade: API no ar
GET {{baseUrl}}/users
Accept: application/json

### 1) Export CSV (chart) - SUCESSO (200 + arquivo CSV)
POST {{baseUrl}}/exports
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: text/csv

{
  "format": "csv",
  "source_type": "chart",
  "mode": "sync",
  "file_name": "chart_kpi",
  "delimiter": ",",
  "payload": {
    "categories": ["2026-02-01", "2026-02-02", "2026-02-03"],
    "series": [
      { "name": "views", "values": [120, 180, 250] },
      { "name": "conversion_rate", "values": [1.2, 1.4, 1.6] }
    ]
  }
}

### 2) Export CSV (chart) com delimitador ";" - SUCESSO
POST {{baseUrl}}/exports
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: text/csv

{
  "format": "csv",
  "source_type": "chart",
  "mode": "sync",
  "file_name": "chart_kpi_semicolon",
  "delimiter": ";",
  "payload": {
    "categories": ["Jan", "Feb"],
    "series": [
      { "name": "revenue", "values": [1000, 1500] }
    ]
  }
}

### 3) Export CSV (table) - SUCESSO (mock de anomalias historicas)
POST {{baseUrl}}/exports
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: text/csv

{
  "format": "csv",
  "source_type": "table",
  "mode": "sync",
  "file_name": "detailed_historical_anomalies",
  "delimiter": ",",
  "payload": {
    "columns": ["date", "metric", "value", "intensity", "variation_percent", "expected_value", "explanation"],
    "rows": [
      [
        "21/01/2026",
        "Downloads",
        "1,560",
        "High",
        "+506.6%",
        "185 - 381",
        "Valor observado (1560) esta +506.6% acima da media historica (257). O modelo detectou que este valor esta fora do padrao esperado. Excede o limite superior esperado (381) em 1179 unidades. Este valor e maior que 100.0% dos dados historicos."
      ],
      [
        "20/01/2026",
        "Downloads",
        "1,964",
        "High",
        "+637.8%",
        "181 - 405",
        "Valor observado (1964) esta +637.8% acima da media historica (266). O modelo detectou que este valor esta fora do padrao esperado. Excede o limite superior esperado (405) em 1559 unidades. Este valor e maior que 100.0% dos dados historicos."
      ]
    ]
  }
}

### 4) Export JPEG (chart) - SUCESSO (mock real derivado da tabela de anomalias)
POST {{baseUrl}}/exports
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: image/jpeg

{
  "format": "jpeg",
  "source_type": "chart",
  "mode": "sync",
  "file_name": "detailed_historical_anomalies_chart",
  "payload": {
    "width": 1280,
    "height": 720,
    "quality": 90,
    "categories": ["15/01/2026", "16/01/2026", "17/01/2026", "18/01/2026", "19/01/2026", "20/01/2026", "21/01/2026"],
    "series": [
      { "name": "observed_downloads", "values": [320, 230, 230, 230, 360, 1964, 1560] },
      { "name": "expected_min", "values": [180, 175, 170, 160, 180, 181, 185] },
      { "name": "expected_max", "values": [380, 370, 340, 300, 410, 405, 381] }
    ]
  }
}

### 5) Export async - AINDA NAO IMPLEMENTADO (esperado 501)
POST {{baseUrl}}/exports
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json

{
  "format": "csv",
  "source_type": "chart",
  "mode": "async",
  "payload": {
    "categories": ["2026-02-01"],
    "series": [
      { "name": "views", "values": [100] }
    ]
  }
}

### 6) Payload invalido (series com tamanho diferente de categories) - esperado 500 no estado atual
### Obs: quando mapearmos erro de dominio para 400 no handler, esse caso deve virar 400.
POST {{baseUrl}}/exports
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json

{
  "format": "csv",
  "source_type": "chart",
  "mode": "sync",
  "payload": {
    "categories": ["2026-02-01", "2026-02-02"],
    "series": [
      { "name": "views", "values": [100] }
    ]
  }
}

### 7) Requisicao invalida (sem payload) - esperado 400
POST {{baseUrl}}/exports
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json

{
  "format": "csv",
  "source_type": "chart",
  "mode": "sync"
}
